com.mojang.serialization

Interface MapLike<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of the serialized form.

    public interface MapLike<T>
    An unmodifiable store for serialized key-value pairs. This interface can be used when access to and iteration over serialized key-value pairs is necessary, but other aspects of Java maps, such as mutability, are unnecessary.

      • get

        @Nullable
T get(T key)
        Retrieves the value corresponding to the given key, or null if there is no mapping for the given key. Note that, unlike Map.get(Object), a return value of null should only occur if this map truly does not contain a mapping.
        Parameters:
        key - The serialized key.
        Returns:
        The value associated with the key, or null if the entry does not exist.

      • get

        @Nullable
T get(String key)
        Retrieves the value corresponding to the given key, or null if there is no mapping for the given key. Note that, unlike Map.get(Object), a return value of null should only occur if this map truly does not contain a mapping.

        The argument should be the String representation of a serialized key.

        Parameters:
        key - The string key.
        Returns:
        The value associated with the key, or null if the entry does not exist.

      • entries

        Stream<(T,T)> entries()
        Returns a fresh Stream of all the entries in this map.

      • forMap

        static <T> MapLike<T> forMap(Map<T,T> map,
                             DynamicOps<T> ops)
        Creates a MapLike containing the entries of the given Map.

        The map is not defensively copied, so modifications to the map are reflected in the returned MapLike.

        Type Parameters:
        T - The type of the serialized form.
        Parameters:
        map - The map to wrap.
        ops - A DynamicOps instance defining the serialized form.
        Returns:
        A MapLike containing the entries of the given map.
